dfischer.proxysniffer

Class ProxySnifferTransaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySnifferTransaction

  • public class ProxySnifferTransaction
extends java.lang.Object
    A declared transaction which effects that during the load test the time between the execution of two arbitrary URLs is measured. Additionally, if the ending URL is a page break this means that the transaction ends at end of the corresponding page.
    Since:
    V5.4-E

      • ProxySnifferTransaction

        public ProxySnifferTransaction(long transactionId,
                       java.lang.String transactionName,
                       long startDataRecordId,
                       long endDataRecordId)
        Create a fully initialized instance.
        Parameters:
        transactionId - ID of the transaction, any unique number is ok
        transactionName - the name of the transaction shown in the GUI and in the test result - must also be unique
        startDataRecordId - the data record ID of the starting URL
        endDataRecordId - the data record ID of the ending URL, or if the ID is a page break then the transaction ends at the end of the corresponding page
        See Also:
        ProxyDataRecord.getId(), ProxyDataRecord.getDataType()
